      "seed": 1040938658,
      "version": 165,
      "versionNonce": 224649278,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1776601027178,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Core Entities\n- Clients\n- Requests\n- Policy\n- RateLimitter Engine",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 6,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Core Entities\n- Clients\n- Requests\n- Policy\n- RateLimitter Engine",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.35
    },
    {
      "id": "9MSBVbu5toSohx2mH9ayI",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1138.0903790398988,
      "y": 217.8145526117807,
      "width": 723.718994140625,
      "height": 459,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "a4",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1975088610,
      "version": 70,
      "versionNonce": 1151547042,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1776615264664,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Different RateLimiting algorithm\n\nFixed Window Counter\n- Counts requests in a fixed time window and resets at interval boundaries\n- Boundary reset allows sudden burst (double-spend around window edges)\n\nSliding Window Log\n- Stores timestamps of requests and keeps only those within the rolling window\n- High memory and cleanup cost due to storing many timestamps\n\nSliding Window Counter\n- Combines current and previous window counts using weighted average\n- Approximate, assumes uniform distribution so can be slightly inaccurate\n\nToken Bucket\n- Uses tokens refilled at a fixed rate; each request consumes a token\n- Allows bursts, so does not strictly enforce limit at every instant",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 6,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Different RateLimiting algorithm\n\nFixed Window Counter\n- Counts requests in a fixed time window and resets at interval boundaries\n- Boundary reset allows sudden burst (double-spend around window edges)\n\nSliding Window Log\n- Stores timestamps of requests and keeps only those within the rolling window\n- High memory and cleanup cost due to storing many timestamps\n\nSliding Window Counter\n- Combines current and previous window counts using weighted average\n- Approximate, assumes uniform distribution so can be slightly inaccurate\n\nToken Bucket\n- Uses tokens refilled at a fixed rate; each request consumes a token\n- Allows bursts, so does not strictly enforce limit at every instant",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.35
    },
